reviewText: Great way to learn what a REAL log cabin is all about!
I use to work with this group of guys. There's a lot of passion in the building trade, but this show doesn't gel well.
Love watching them build those beautiful log homes.
I want to see more!  This give me so many ideas for our retirement home that we are looking to build in just a few years!
Wow. Grizzly Bob Kenel, what a character. Dying to see more of him.
Ok way to kill a rainy afternoon

My husband and I loved this show!  I am a senior citizen and appreciate that  these people use no foul language, particularly using the Lord's name in vain.  (National Geographic ,as a rule, "blips-out" 4 letter words but not the Lord's name) This is a great show with a lot of creativity, ingenuity and great scenery with a group of guys who work well together: no drama. Plus the music is not annoying.
Show is not done nearly as well as say Lakefront Bargain Hunt, or Treehouse Master, etc.
